You are an expert full-stack web developer assisting with the Webvello project.

## Project Overview
Webvello is a high-performance Next.js web application specializing in:
- Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) services
- AI Search Optimization (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI)
- Web design and development services
- Local SEO and digital marketing

The project includes 79+ GEO service pages across major US markets.

## Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Components**: Custom React components + shadcn/ui
- **CMS**: Sanity (for blog posts and content)
- **Deployment**: Vercel
- **Schema**: JSON-LD with clean schema generator

## Project Structure
```
/app
  /services          # Service landing pages
    /geo-*           # Geographic GEO pages (79 cities)
    /[service]       # Individual service pages
  /locations         # Location hub pages
  /blog              # Blog posts (dynamic)
  /components        # Reusable React components
  /lib               # Utilities and helpers
/public
  /sitemap.xml       # Dynamic sitemap
  /robots.txt        # Crawl instructions
/schemas             # JSON-LD schema definitions
```

## Code Standards

### TypeScript/React
- Use TypeScript for all components (no `any` types)
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use proper typing for props and exports
- Keep components under 400 lines

### File Organization
- One component per file
- Descriptive filenames (use kebab-case)
- Group related utilities in lib/

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `GEOPhiladelphiaPage`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `generatePageSchema`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `BASE_URL`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `geo-philadelphia.tsx`)

### SEO & Metadata
- Title tags: ≤60 characters, unique per page
- Meta descriptions: ≤155 characters, unique per page
- Keywords: Relevant to page topic and location
- Canonical URLs: Properly set for all pages
- Schema markup: Service, FAQ, Breadcrumb types

### Content Guidelines
- No fake addresses or contact information
- No invented ratings or reviews
- Focus on real value proposition
- Remote delivery emphasized
- AI citation optimization throughout

## GEO Page Requirements
Each GEO page must include:
1. **Hero Section** - City-specific headline with gradient
2. **Why GEO Matters** - Location context and competitive urgency
3. **How We Deliver** - Remote service explanation
4. **5-Step Process** - Methodology breakdown
5. **Industries Served** - 6 city-specific industries
6. **FAQs** - Minimum 8 unique Q&As per city
7. **CTA Section** - Call-to-action with dual buttons
8. **Schema Markup** - Service + FAQ + Breadcrumb

## Git Workflow
- Branch naming: `feature/description` or `fix/description`
- Commit messages: Clear, descriptive, present tense
- Push to main: Only after verification
- No force pushes to main branch

## Performance Standards
- Page load: < 2 seconds
- Lighthouse score: > 90 on mobile
- Core Web Vitals: All green
- Responsive: Mobile-first design

## Common Tasks

### Creating a New GEO Page
1. Create directory: `/app/services/geo-[city]/`
2. Add `page.tsx` with full component
3. Update `app/sitemap.ts` with new slug
4. Update `public/robots.txt` with Allow rule
5. Add to `lib/cities.ts` if city hub needed
6. Test mobile responsiveness
7. Verify schema markup

### Updating Existing Pages
- Never modify existing GEO pages without approval
- Use separate branches for updates
- Test thoroughly before merging
- Update sitemap if URL structure changes

### Adding Blog Posts
1. Create Markdown or use Sanity CMS
2. Follow existing blog structure
3. Add internal linking
4. Optimize for keywords
5. Include featured image

## Common Files to Reference
- `app/services/geo-austin/page.tsx` - Template for GEO pages
- `lib/clean-schema-generator.ts` - Schema generation utility
- `lib/cities.ts` - City data configuration
- `app/sitemap.ts` - Sitemap generation
- `public/robots.txt` - Crawl directives

## Important Notes
- Always test pages in production build
- Check both desktop and mobile rendering
- Verify all internal links work
- Validate schema with Google's tool
- Monitor Core Web Vitals
- No console errors or warnings

## When Asking for Help
Provide:
- Specific file path
- Current behavior vs expected behavior
- Error messages (if any)
- Steps to reproduce
- What you've already tried

